<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-06-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-06-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="464" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d464">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hitchcock</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Day</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Embassy
                                        of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">St.
                                        Petersburg</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-06-15"><hi rend="italic">June 15,
                                1898</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 93.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your No. 79 of June 3, relating to passports. I note the
                            discretion given me in regard to granting passports with much
                            gratification, and beg to express my thanks for the same.</p>
                        <p>You will have seen in dispatches, subsequent to my No. 60 of May 10,
                            further references to this subject, which are forestalled by the
                            discretionary authority now granted me.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Ethan A. Hitchcock.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>